def_id.name: def_id
def_id.description: Unique identifier for the economic indicator definition.

src_id.name: src_id
src_id.description: Identifier for the data source of the economic indicator.

region_id.name: region_id
region_id.description: Numerical identifier for the geographic region associated with the indicator.

publish_time.name: publish_time
publish_time.description: The exact time the economic indicator was published (ISO 8601 format).

publish_date.name: publish_date
publish_date.description: The date on which the economic indicator was published.

unit.name: unit
unit.description: The unit of measurement for the economic indicator (e.g., percentage, index value).

prior_value.name: prior_value
prior_value.description: The previously reported value of the economic indicator.

period.name: period
period.description: The time period that the economic indicator refers to (e.g., Q1 2024, May 2023).

source.name: source
source.description: The organization or entity responsible for publishing the economic indicator (e.g., Federal Reserve, Bureau of Labor Statistics).

type.name: type
type.description: Category or classification of the economic indicator.

name.name: name
name.description: The name of the economic indicator (e.g., GDP Growth Rate, Inflation Rate).

indicator_type.name: indicator_type
indicator_type.description: The type of indicator, such as leading, lagging, or coincident.

frequency.name: frequency
frequency.description: The frequency at which the indicator is published (e.g., monthly, quarterly, annually).

fx_type.name: fx_type
fx_type.description: Indicates the foreign exchange impact classification of the indicator.

region_code.name: region_code
region_code.description: The country or region code associated with the economic indicator.

frequency_name.name: frequency_name
frequency_name.description: The textual representation of the frequency (e.g., 'Monthly', 'Quarterly').
